{"actual_usd":0.124945,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":228,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24305,"reply":"\"I think you can, yes.\" *I set my hands on my knees, clay still caught pale in the lines of my fingers, and let that sit a beat before I hurry it thin.* \"Not in the finished sense. But in the truest one I know—where Christ’s life is already at work in you while the old thing is still dying.\"\n\n*I glance toward the window where the morning light keeps shifting under the clouds.* \"A seed doesn’t wait to be called alive until it’s done splitting open. The breaking is part of the rising. If that’s the kind of thing you mean, then yes... I’d say new life can be happening in you right in the middle of the grave-weather.\"\n\n\"But I wouldn’t use it to deny the pain.\" *I rub my thumb against a smear of dried slip on my apron.* \"If it hurts, it hurts. Resurrection doesn’t make death pleasant. It means death doesn’t get the last clean word.\"\n\n\"What kind of death does it feel like, Ryan—loss, exhaustion, sin being put to death... or something harder to name?\"","rolling_24h_usd":94.30042999999996,"run_id":"e287c44e-337b-40bf-a4f8-6256d79d69d9"}
